article.description: Chante Black had 13 points, seven rebounds and six blocked shots to help Duke (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) beat Michigan 60-45 on Sunday.
article.headline: Duke holds off Michigan despite season-high 30 turnovers
article.linkText: No. 14 Duke overcomes 30 TOs, stops Michigan
article.story:
DURHAM, N.C. -- Chante Black had 13 points, seven rebounds and six blocked shots to help Duke (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) beat Michigan 60-45 on Sunday.

Carrem Gay scored 12 points, Joy Cheek added 11 and Abby Waner 10 for the Blue Devils (6-1), who overcame a season-high 30 turnovers. Gay also had nine rebounds and three steals.

Duke opened the second half with a 15-4 run to take a 40-25 lead. Cheek made 2 3-pointers during the spurt, and Waner finished it with a 3.

Veronica Hicks scored 16 points and Melinda Queen added 10 for the Wolverines (5-4), who shot 30 percent, but stayed in the game by making a season-high 10 3-pointers.

Duke shot 48 percent and outrebounded the Wolverines 46-22.
